      "module_path": "dry_check",
      "docs": "SHA-256 fingerprint (64-char lowercase hex string) over the full set of (repo_relative_path, content_hash) pairs scanned by the corpus indexer during a `dry write` run. Written into the coverage manifest by `dry write` so readers can identify which workspace corpus produced the manifest. Comparing the stored value with a separately computed current corpus fingerprint detects corpus changes (added, removed, or modified files) and marks the coverage stale; this domain value does not prescribe the approval-usecase wiring for that comparison. The all-zeros sentinel (fail_closed()) is written on failed runs as fail-closed provenance. Mirrors DryCheckConfigFingerprint in structure and fail-closed convention.",
      "spec_refs": [
        {
          "file": "track/items/dfp-rfp-loop-cost-reduction-2026-06-13/spec.json",
          "anchor": "AC-10"
        },
        {
          "file": "track/items/dfp-rfp-loop-cost-reduction-2026-06-13/spec.json",
          "anchor": "AC-11"
        }
      ],
      "informal_grounds": [
        {
          "kind": "feedback",
          "summary": "The corpus fingerprint concept (SHA-256 over sorted (path, content_hash) pairs of all candidate corpus files) is an implementation detail added in Round 9. No spec anchor directly states the corpus fingerprint field; AC-10 and AC-11 capture the coverage-record-based staleness gate that this fingerprint can support when a current corpus fingerprint is available for comparison. CN-08 grounds the fail-closed response when coverage is missing or inconsistent. The format invariant (64-char lowercase hex) mirrors DryCheckConfigFingerprint's constructor invariant."
        }
      ]
    },
