      "module_path": "dry_check",
      "docs": "Coverage manifest written by `dry write` and consumed by `dry check-approved` for staleness checking (D5). Records the set of FragmentRef values (path + content_hash) for all diff fragments processed in the most recent `dry write` run (fragment_refs), plus the set of DryCheckPairKey values for all pairs that were considered current in that run (processed_pair_keys), plus the config_fingerprint of the dry-check.json settings used by that run, plus the corpus_fingerprint of the workspace corpus files scanned by the indexer. If a current diff fragment's FragmentRef is absent from fragment_refs, `check-approved` returns Blocked (stale coverage). If a historical Violation record's pair_key is absent from processed_pair_keys, that record is treated as stale (candidate side fixed) and skipped by the gate. If the stored config_fingerprint differs from the current config fingerprint, `check-approved` returns Blocked (config changed). The stored corpus_fingerprint is provenance for detecting that the manifest was built from a different workspace corpus when compared with a current corpus fingerprint; such a mismatch means coverage is stale and must be regenerated. BTreeSet preserves deterministic serialization order (CN-05).",
      "spec_refs": [
        {
          "file": "track/items/dfp-rfp-loop-cost-reduction-2026-06-13/spec.json",
          "anchor": "IN-05"
